name: Central Park Community Orchard
short_description: Public fruit trees in the city heart.
description: A collection of heritage apple and pear trees located near the lake and the viaduct, managed for public picking.

name: Danbury Common Sweet Chestnuts
description: The heathland and wooded fringes of the common are home to massive, mature sweet chestnut trees.

name: River Chelmer Wild Garlic
description: Damp, shaded areas along the Chelmer Valley Way, particularly near Bunny Walks, are rich in wild garlic.

name: Incredible Edible Chelmsford - High St
description: Public planters featuring rosemary, thyme, and seasonal edible flowers for public use.

name: Hylands Park Walnuts
description: The parkland surrounding the historic house features several mature walnut trees near the public footpaths.

name: Maldon Estuary Samphire (Fringe)
description: Accessible salt marsh areas near the tidal limit of the Chelmer & Blackwater Navigation.

name: Broomfield Orchard
description: A small stand of apple and plum trees planted on public green space for the community.

name: Galleywood Common Blackberries
description: The scrubland around the old racecourse is one of the best spots for huge blackberry yields.

name: Chelmer & Blackwater Sloes
description: The towpath heading towards Sandford Mill is lined with blackthorn bushes (sloes).

name: Melbourne Edible Planters
description: Public planters near the local shops featuring kale, chives, and occasional strawberry plants.

name: Admirals Park Elder
description: Elder bushes are abundant along the river path connecting Central Park to Admirals Park.

name: Great Baddow Hazelnuts
description: Hazel trees line the public bridleways and footpaths leading out toward Sandon.

name: Chancellor Park Rosehips
description: The landscaped meadows and balancing ponds feature wild rose bushes rich in autumn hips.

name: Baddow Meads Wild Greens
description: Damp meadows near the river are excellent for gathering wild sorrel and watermint.

name: Writtle Village Wild Plums
description: Public paths near the duck pond and village green feature occasional wild plum and bullace trees.
